%main.govuk-main-wrapper#main-content{role: 'main'}
  .govuk-grid-row
    .govuk-grid-column-two-thirds
      %h1.govuk-heading-xl
        Accessibility statement for Check if youâ€™ll be charged to drive in a Clean Air Zone
      %p
        This website is run by the Joint Air Quality Unit (JAQU) supported by the Department of
        Transport and Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs. We want as many people as
        possible to be able to use this website.
      %p
        For example, that means you should be able to:
        %ul.govuk-list-govuk-list--bullet
          %li
            %p
              zoom in up to 300% without the text spilling off the screen.
          %li
            %p
              navigate most of the website using just a keyboard.
          %li
            %p
              navigate most of the website using speech recognition software.
          %li
            %p
              listen to most of the website using a screen reader (including the most recent
              versions of JAWS, NVDA and VoiceOver).
      %p We've also made the website text as simple as possible to understand.
      %p
        = external_link_to('AbilityNet',
                           'https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/',
                           id: 'ability-net-link')
        has advice on making your device easier to use if you have a disability.

      %h2.govuk-heading-m Reporting accessibility problems with this website
      %p
        We're always looking to improve the accessibility of this website. If you find any problems
        that are not listed on this page or think we're not meeting accessibility requirements,
        let us know using our
        = succeed '.' do
          = external_link_to('feedback form',
                             Rails.configuration.x.contact_form_link,
                             id: 'feedback-form-link')

      %h2.govuk-heading-m Enforcement procedure
      %p
        The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is responsible for enforcing the Public
        Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018
        (the 'accessibility regulations'). If you're not happy with how we respond to your
        complaint,
        = succeed '.' do
          = external_link_to('contact the Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS)',
                             'https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com/',
                             id: 'eass-link')

      %h2.govuk-heading-m Technical information about this website's accessibility
      %p
        JAQU is committed to making its website accessible, in accordance with the Public Sector
        Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.
      %p
        This website is fully compliant with the
        = external_link_to('Web Content Accessibility Guidelines version 2.1',
                           'https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/',
                           id: 'guidelines-link')
        AA standard.

      %h2.govuk-heading-m How we tested this website
      %p
        This website was last tested at least monthly by the team that maintains it, and
        periodically by external bodies. At the time of publishing, it was last tested externally on
        26 November 2019 by Digital Accessibility Centre Limited.
      %p We tested all routes through the service
      %p This statement was prepared on 7 January 2020.
